        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: floor incomplete ClawScan coverage",
        "body": "## What this PR does\n\nThis PR makes the prompt-backed ClawScan evaluator fail closed when ClawHub did not review the full material artifact text.\n\n## Scenario this protects\n\nThe legacy/local evaluator builds a prompt from `SKILL.md` and uploaded file contents. That prompt path has size limits.\n\nIf `SKILL.md` is truncated, file contents are truncated, or later file blocks are omitted after the aggregate prompt limit, a benign model answer should not be stored as clean. In that situation, there is still unreviewed artifact text that may matter.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds an explicit artifact coverage signal for the prompt-backed evaluator path.\n- Records incomplete coverage when prompt assembly truncates `SKILL.md`.\n- Records incomplete coverage when prompt assembly truncates file content.\n- Records incomplete coverage when file blocks are omitted after the aggregate prompt limit.\n- Records incomplete coverage when hidden comments are stripped before review.\n- Converts benign answers from incomplete coverage into suspicious/review results before storage.\n- Keeps incomplete coverage visible in moderation with `review.artifact_incomplete`.\n\n## What maintainers should expect\n\nA clean-looking result from incomplete prompt coverage can no longer silently clear review state. The caller gets a review-floor result instead, with the reason preserved.\n\nThe modern GitHub Actions Codex worker path is different: it materializes artifact files into a workspace for Codex instead of relying on the sliced prompt text. This PR still preserves parsed `artifactCoverage` if that parser path receives it.\n\nSkillSpector and static scan findings remain advisory/context inputs. They do not replace the ClawScan verdict, so the review floor belongs at the LLM result/moderation boundary.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `bun test convex/lib/securityPrompt.test.ts scripts/local-clawscan-dry-run.test.ts convex/lib/moderationEngine.test.ts`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/securityScan.test.ts convex/llmEval.test.ts scripts/security/run-codex-scan-worker.test.ts`\n- `bunx convex codegen`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/schema/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `bun run ci:packages`\n\n`bun test convex/llmEval.test.ts convex/securityScan.test.ts scripts/security/run-codex-scan-worker.test.ts` was also tried, but `convex/securityScan.test.ts` requires Vitest APIs such as `vi.stubEnv` and `vi.mocked`; the same files passed under Vitest as listed above.\n",
        "branch": "brzezowski/clawscan-artifact-coverage-floor",
